Integration by parts followed by divergence results in weak form as: (∇Ψ,c∇φ) - <Ψ, c∇φ . n> (please verify) But, this results in coupled variable in boundary condition. Thanks
Please check the maths:

∇.(Ψ(c∇φ)) = Ψ∇.(c∇φ) + c∇φ.∇Ψ
Ψ∇.(c∇φ) = ∇.(Ψ(c∇φ)) - c∇φ.∇Ψ
taking volume integral and using divergence theorem
-int (Ψ∇.(c∇φ)) dV = -int (Ψ(c∇φ.n))dS + int( c∇φ.∇Ψ) dv
weak form.              =  - <Ψ, c∇φ . n>      +  (∇Ψ,c∇φ) 

kernel coded as:
{
  return   _grad_test[_i][_qp] * _u[_qp] * _grad_phi[_qp];
}

However, I have found a different math used in code at:
https://github.com/anilkunwar/danphe/blob/working_codes/src/kernel/NernstPlanckConvection.C
line 63
{
return ion_velocity * _grad_u[_qp] * _test[_i][_qp];
}

Here grad of _u[_qp] is taken instead of the test function.
